[node name="RulesLabel" type="RichTextLabel" parent="HowToPlayPanel/CenterContainer/PanelContainer/MarginContainer/VBox/ScrollContainer" unique_id=1495829800]
layout_mode = 2
size_flags_horizontal = 3
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]GOAL[/b]
Defeat your opponent by either:
  • Occupying [b]all[/b] of their [b]Residential[/b] cells
  • Starving them out — if they cannot afford their residential upkeep for several consecutive turns, they lose

[b]RESOURCES[/b]
Each turn, connected cells generate income:
  • [b]Manpower (MP)[/b] — spent on most actions
  • [b]Supplies (SUP)[/b] — consumed by residential cells each turn
  • [b]Materials (MAT)[/b] — consumed by residential cells each turn

Only cells [b]connected[/b] to your starting base produce income. An isolated cell generates nothing.

[b]CELL TYPES[/b]
  • [b]Residential[/b] — generates MP. Consumes SUP and MAT each turn.
  • [b]Resource[/b] — generates SUP. Consumes MP.
  • [b]Industry[/b] — generates MAT. Consumes SUP and MP.

[b]ACTIONS[/b] (all cost Manpower)
  • [b]Occupy[/b] — claim an adjacent unowned cell, or take an enemy cell (costs more MP)
  • [b]Upgrade[/b] — improve a cell to the next level, increasing its output (takes several turns)
  • [b]Raze[/b] — raze a cell; it downgrades it's level and it becomes neutral after a cooldown period
  • [b]Build Residential / Industrial[/b] — convert a cell to a different type
  • [b]Mobilize[/b] — generate extra manpower by distributing extra resources, locks upgrading for few turns

[b]TURNS[/b]
Players alternate turns. End your turn with the [b]End Turn[/b] button when you are done acting."
fit_content = true

